ad (newspaperarchive.com, viewed February 1, 2018). Latest issue consulted: Volume XVII, whole number 12779 (April 2, 1888) (newspaperarchive.com, viewed February 1, 2018). Butte miner (Butte, Mont. : Daily)"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:36.478Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2018218532/", "image_url": [], "index": 3, "language": ["english"], "location": ["butte", "montana", "united states", "silver bow"], "number": ["online resource", "2018218532", "2018218531", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "958730662", "2576-7135"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "the butte daily miner (butte city, montana) 1885-18?? [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 37.836105, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["butte", "newspapers", "united states", "montana", "silver bow", "butte (mont.)"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:55:54.213Z", "title": "The Butte daily miner", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2018218532/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2013272186/"], "campaigns": [], "date": "1901", "dates": ["[1901 TO 1912]"], "description": ["Daily (except Sun.) Began May 2, 1901; ceased -v. 29, no. 299 (Dec. 31, 1912). \"Republican.\" Cf. Ayer, 1912. Suspended: Feb. 13-Mar. 27, 1907. Description based on: Vol. XXI, no. 240 (January 2, 1902); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed December 18, 2013). Latest issue consulted: Vol. XXIII, no. 145 (December 31, 1903) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed December 18, 2013). Butte daily post (Online)"], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2026-05-19T21:37:23.371Z", "group": ["ndnp/newspapers", "united-states-newspaper-directory"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2013272186/", "image_url": [], "index": 4, "language": ["english"], "location": ["butte", "montana", "united states", "silver bow"], "number": ["online resource", "2332-7510", "862977549", "2026-04-13t21:30:13", "2013272186"], "original_format": ["newspaper"], "other_title": ["Butte intermountain"], "partof": ["serial and government publications division", "the butte inter mountain (butte, montona) 1901-1912 [online resource]", "directory of u.s. newspapers in american libraries"], "publication_frequency": ["daily"], "score": 37.836105, "shelf_id": "ISSN RECORD", "site": ["usnd"], "subject": ["butte", "newspapers", "united states", "montana", "silver bow", "butte (mont.)"], "timestamp": "2026-05-26T20:49:47.660Z", "title": "The Butte inter mountain", "type": ["title"], "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2013272186/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2014218270/"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["metal trades council of butte (mont.)", "state metal trades council (mont.)", "montana world war veterans, inc", "montana state federation of labor", "silver bow trades and labor assembly (mont.)"], "date": "1918", "dates": ["[1918 TO 1921]"], "description": ["Daily (except Sun.) Began August 20, 1918; ceased v. 3, no. 244 (June 1, 1921). \"Independent.\" Motto: \"We preach the class struggle in the interests of the workers as a class.\" Suspended: Aug. 22-24, 1918, and Sept. 14, 1918. Available on microfilm from Micro Photo Division, Bell and Howell. Official organ of: Montana State Federation of Labor, National Trades Council of Butte, Silver Bow Trades and Labor Assembly, State Metal Trades Council, Feb. 25, 1920-June 1, 1921; Montana World War Veterans, Inc., Nov. 22, 1920-June 1, 1921. Description based on: Volume 1, number 129 (January 16, 1919); title from masthead (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed April 16, 2014). Latest issue consulted: Vol. III, no. 115 (December 31, 1920) (Chroniclingamerica.loc.gov, viewed April 16, 2014). Butte bulletin (Online)"], "digitiz